## Cohort Discovery Data Fix — 2026-05-12

### Context
Cohort discovery rule `CustWithElectricityContracts` returned 82 path survivors
but 0 cohorts in the preview. Root cause was traced to the Cust360Auto synthetic
dataset: every contract had a unique `contract_id`, owned by exactly one customer,
so the graph had zero shared contract nodes. With no shared nodes, cohort edges
are mathematically impossible regardless of the engine logic.

### Changes

1. `data/customer/generate_data.py`
   - **`gen_contracts`**: Added a shared electricity contract pool (`electricity_pool`
     parameter, default 40 slots with IDs `ECON#####`). A configurable fraction
     (`pool_share_rate`, default 0.35) of contract rows are sampled from this pool,
     assigning different customers to the same contract URI. This creates multi-customer
     contract nodes in the graph, enabling cohort edge formation.
   - **`run`**: Passes `electricity_pool` and `pool_share_rate` from CLI args to
     `gen_contracts`.
   - **`_build_insert_sql`**: Fixed `%s` → `?` parameter placeholders (Databricks
     SQL connector DBAPI requirement; `%s` was rejected with PARSE_SYNTAX_ERROR).
   - **`main`**: Added `--electricity-pool` and `--pool-share-rate` CLI arguments.

2. Regenerated `benoit_cayla.customer` tables with `--drop-existing --seed 42`:
   - 40 shared electricity contracts (`ECON00001`–`ECON00040`)
   - Top shared contracts held by up to 7 customers (e.g. ECON00022, ECON00037)
   - All other tables unchanged in shape and scale (200 customers, 300 contract rows, etc.)

3. App restarted and redeployed (`ontobricks-030`, state: RUNNING).

### Modified files
- `data/customer/generate_data.py`

### Next steps (manual, in the app)
- Open the Cust360Auto domain → **Build** → run a full rebuild to regenerate the
  triplestore and Ladybug graph from the new source data.
- After rebuild, run the `CustWithElectricityContracts` cohort rule — the preview
  should now return cohort groups.

