## Fix: Synced Table PK Violation — Duplicate Triples in R2RML View — 2026-05-12

### Context
Building a Digital Twin with `managed_synced` mode failed during Lakeflow sync
with `SYNCED_TABLE_USER_ERROR.PRIMARY_KEY_CONSTRAINT_VIOLATION`. The source UC
view `triplestore_cust360auto_v4` used `UNION ALL` across 19 source branches but
the outermost `SELECT` lacked `DISTINCT`, allowing duplicate `(subject, predicate,
object)` triples through. Lakebase Postgres rejected them on insert because the
synced table declares those three columns as its PK.

Root cause: the SPARQL template that drives R2RML-to-Spark SQL translation used
`SELECT ?subject ?predicate ?object` (no `DISTINCT`). The `SparqlTranslator`
correctly propagates `is_distinct=False` all the way to the final SQL, producing
`SELECT subject, predicate, object FROM (...) AS triples`.

### Changes
1. `src/back/objects/digitaltwin/_build_pipeline.py` — changed the all-data
   SPARQL template from `SELECT ?subject ?predicate ?object` to
   `SELECT DISTINCT ?subject ?predicate ?object`.
2. `src/back/objects/registry/scheduler.py` (`_generate_sql_from_r2rml`) — same
   one-word fix in the parallel scheduled-build path.
3. Databricks: regenerated the existing `benoit_cayla.ontobricks.triplestore_cust360auto_v4`
   view with `SELECT DISTINCT` at the outer level (512 duplicates eliminated;
   row count dropped from 16 794 → 16 282).

### Modified files
- `src/back/objects/digitaltwin/_build_pipeline.py`
- `src/back/objects/registry/scheduler.py`

### Test results
1678 passed, 81 skipped — pre-existing failures unrelated to this change
(Python 3.9 `str | None` syntax in `dtwin.py`, stale mock paths).

