## Fix: Union View Creation Fails When sync_uc_schema ≠ Postgres Schema — 2026-05-12

### Context
After the previous two fixes, the build succeeded but failed at the
`ensure_synced_union_view` step with:

> `relation "cust360auto_v4_sync" does not exist`

Root cause: `LakebaseFlatStore.ensure_synced_union_view` used an unqualified
`synced` reference in the `CREATE OR REPLACE VIEW` DDL. The `search_path` for
`_cursor()` is set to the Postgres graph schema (`ontobricks_graph`). But the
Lakebase `_sync` table is created in the Postgres schema that corresponds to the
**UC schema segment** of the synced-table FQN — which is now `ontobricks` (from
the registry). So Postgres resolved `cust360auto_v4_sync` to
`ontobricks_graph.cust360auto_v4_sync` while the table actually lives at
`ontobricks.cust360auto_v4_sync`.

### Change
`src/back/core/graphdb/lakebase/LakebaseFlatStore.py`
(`ensure_synced_union_view`): when `sync_uc_schema` ≠ `_schema`, the `_sync`
table reference is explicitly schema-qualified
(`"ontobricks".g_v1_sync`) so the DDL is independent of `search_path`.

```sql
-- Before (broke when schemas differ)
FROM g_v1_sync

-- After
FROM "ontobricks".g_v1_sync
```

When the two schemas are the same (simple / single-namespace deployment), the
unqualified reference is kept as before.

### Also updated
`tests/test_lakebase_flat_store.py`:
- `test_ensure_synced_union_view_qualifies_sync_table_when_schemas_differ` (new)
- `test_synced_uc_name_uses_explicit_sync_uc_schema` (new)
- `test_drop_table_uses_sync_uc_schema_in_fqn` (new)
- Renamed and corrected `test_prefers_registry_volume_schema` →
  `test_explicit_config_schema_wins_over_registry` to match current resolver
  behaviour; added `test_falls_back_to_registry_when_config_schema_empty`.

### Modified files
- `src/back/core/graphdb/lakebase/LakebaseFlatStore.py`
- `tests/test_lakebase_flat_store.py`

### Test results
211 failed (pre-existing), 1681 passed, 81 skipped — no regression.

