## Refactor: Revert sync_uc_schema — One Postgres Schema for All Graph Objects — 2026-05-12

### Context
The previous fix added a `sync_uc_schema` concept to allow the UC synced-table
FQN schema segment to differ from the Postgres graph schema. This introduced a
two-schema situation in Postgres (`_sync` table in `ontobricks`, companion and
union view in `ontobricks_graph`) which broke `ensure_synced_union_view`.

The correct design is **one Postgres schema** for all graph objects (`_sync`,
companion, union view). The UC FQN schema segment is always the Postgres graph
schema (`graph_engine_config.schema`), keeping all Lakebase objects aligned.

