## Security: urllib3 2.7.0 + GitPython 3.1.50 vulnerability fixes — 2026-05-12

### Context
Three high-severity Dependabot alerts (#26, #27, #28) against transitive
dependencies in `uv.lock`:

- **#27** `urllib3` GHSA-mf9v-mfxr-j63j — decompression-bomb safeguards
  bypassed in parts of the streaming API.
- **#28** `urllib3` GHSA-qccp-gfcp-xxvc — sensitive headers forwarded across
  origins in proxied low-level redirects.
- **#26** `GitPython` — newline injection in `config_writer()` section param
  bypasses the CVE-2026-42215 patch, enabling RCE via `core.hooksPath`.

The Databricks internal PyPI proxy index does not yet list urllib3 2.7.0 or
GitPython 3.1.50.  Both wheels were downloaded directly from pythonhosted.org
(which IS reachable), locked via `UV_FIND_LINKS`, then the lock entries were
patched to reference the canonical pythonhosted.org URLs so the committed
`uv.lock` remains reproducible on any machine that can reach pythonhosted.org.

### Changes
1. `pyproject.toml`
   - `[tool.uv].constraint-dependencies`: bumped `gitpython>=3.1.49` →
     `>=3.1.50`; uncommented and enabled `urllib3>=2.7.0` (was commented out
