## Fix: SWRL inference SQL — chained property atoms produce empty object — 2026-05-12

### Context
Multi-hop SWRL rules (e.g. `P(?x,?y) ∧ Q(?y,?z) → R(?x,?z)`) generated
`'' AS object` for the consequent because `build_inference_sql` only joined
property atoms directly connected to `primary_var` (one-hop). The second-hop
variable `?z` was never added to `var_bindings`, so `obj_expr` fell through to
the `else "''"` branch. All 112 inferred triples had an empty `object` field →
`is_uri('')` returned False → **0 triples ever reached Lakebase**, despite the
Materialise button returning a 200 success response.

`build_violation_sql` already solved this correctly using
`SWRLParser.find_connected_vars` + `order_connected_props` for a full BFS
traversal. `build_inference_sql` was missing the same logic.

### Changes
`src/back/core/reasoning/SWRLSQLTranslator.py`
- Replaced the `primary_props` (direct-only) loop with a BFS traversal using
  `SWRLParser.find_connected_vars` + `order_connected_props`, matching the
  pattern already used in `build_violation_sql`
- Each JOIN now checks which side (`subj_var` or `obj_var`) is already bound
  and uses that as the anchor, so chained hops are resolved in topological order
- Two-hop+ rules now emit the correct column reference (`a3.subject` or
  `a2.object`) instead of `''` for the consequent object

`src/api/routers/internal/dtwin.py`
- Removed the temporary debug log added during diagnosis

### Modified files
- `src/back/core/reasoning/SWRLSQLTranslator.py`
- `src/api/routers/internal/dtwin.py`

### Test results
17 passed, 1 skipped — no regression.

