## Cohort Discovery: apply all fixes from v0.3.1 to current codebase

### Context

The v0.3.1 changelog (2026-05-12) documented four cohort bugs that were fixed
in that branch but were not yet present in the main v0.4.0 codebase. This
entry records their application.

### Changes

1. **src/back/core/graph_analysis/CohortBuilder.py**
   - Added `_predicate_alias_map()` instance method — scans loaded triples and
     builds `{local_name → canonical_data_namespace_uri}` for predicates in
     the data namespace. Cached in `self._cache["predicate_alias"]`.
   - Added `_resolve_predicate(uri)` — calls `_to_data_uri` first (same-namespace
     `#`→`/` rewrite); if unchanged (foreign namespace), falls back to the alias
     map by local name. Mirrors `SWRLSQLTranslator._predicate_local_name_key`.
   - Converted `_outgoing_edge_index` from `@staticmethod` to instance method;
     every triple predicate is now normalised with `_resolve_predicate` before
     being stored as an index key. This fixes the silent-zero-neighbour bug for
     data loaded outside R2RML (direct inserts, W3C OWL round-trips, manual loads)
     where predicates are in ontology form (`#hasClaim`) but the path walker
     looks up data form (`/hasClaim`).
   - Updated `_normalized_links` and `_normalized_compat` to call
     `_resolve_predicate` instead of bare `_to_data_uri` for hop `via`,
     hop `where[*].property`, and compatibility `property`. This fixes the
     cross-namespace predicate bug (e.g. `ontobricks.com/ontology#hasclaim`
     in a domain whose base is `databricks-ontology.com/Cust360Auto#`).

2. **src/front/static/query/js/query-cohorts.js**
   - Added `_dataPropsForClass(classUri)` helper — filters `this.properties` to
     data (non-object) properties whose `domain` matches the class; falls back
     to all data properties if nothing matches. Mirrors `_objectPropsForSource`.
   - `_renderHopWhereRow`: replaced `this.properties` with
     `_dataPropsForClass(targetClassUri)` so the attribute dropdown shows only
     the hop target entity's own data properties.
   - `_renderCompat`: replaced `this.properties` with
     `_dataPropsForClass(this.rule.class_uri)` so the compatibility attribute
     dropdown shows only the root entity's own data properties.
   - `_renderTraceLink`: added `in_frontier === 0` guard before the
     `neighbours_raw === 0` check. When the frontier is empty the diagnostic now
     says "the starting frontier for this hop is empty — all members were
     eliminated before reaching it" instead of wrongly blaming the predicate URI.

3. **tests/test_cohort_builder.py** — added to `TestOntologyDataNamespaceDrift`:
   - `_graph_with_ontology_form_predicates()` fixture — data triples whose
     predicates are in ontology (`#`) form.
   - `test_data_with_ontology_form_predicate_is_indexed_correctly` — verifies the
     engine finds the correct cohort (Alice ↔ Bob via P1) even when data triple
     predicates are in ontology form.
   - `test_trace_shows_nonzero_raw_for_ontology_form_predicate` — verifies
     `neighbours_raw > 0` in `trace_paths` output, ensuring the "no neighbours"
     diagnostic is not triggered incorrectly.
   - `test_via_from_foreign_namespace_resolved_by_local_name` — exact replica of
     the Cust360Auto production scenario: domain base `…/Cust360Auto#`, property
     URIs `ontobricks.com/ontology#hasclaim` (foreign namespace), data triples
     `…/Cust360Auto/hasclaim`. Proves the local-name alias fallback works
     end-to-end.

